text: Football Kingz Football Club was a professional football club from Auckland. The club was the first of its kind in New Zealand. The club played in the Australian National Soccer League (NSL) from 1999 until the league folded in 2004. The club then became the New Zealand Knights and again played in an Australian league, with the Knights playing in the first A-League season in 2005. ==References== Category:Football clubs in Auckland
title: Football Kingz FC
